  "text": "Phosphoenolpyruvate carboxykinases (PEPCK) catalyse the reversible decarboxylation and phosphorylation of oxaloacetate to form phosphoenolpyruvate. Mutations of the PEPCK gene from M. bovis BCG are characterised by attenuated virulence and reduced survival in macrophages [CITATION_1] . The PEPCK gene from M. tuberculosis was shown to be required for replication in murine bone marrow macrophages and mice [CITATION_2] .",
